Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read what you can and cannot do

This page gives you guidance on how to stay safely in Turks and Caicos as a visitor, if you are unable to return to the UK.
Everyone should comply with the measures put in place in Turks and Caicos to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
Moving around in Turks and Caicos
For information on entering Turks and Caicos, see Entry Requirements.
A night curfew, from 8pm until 5am, is in effect from 4 May until 24 May 2020.
All schools, nurseries, Community College and UWI Open Campus will remain closed until 1 June 2020.
A ban is in place on all gatherings in public places of over 25 people, including schools, places of worship, places of entertainment or refreshment, funerals, sporting events and other social gatherings. Movement of people between islands is discouraged.
From 10 May 2020, church and funeral services will be limited to 10 people.
More information on local measures in place is available on the TCI Government website.
Health
Your emotional and mental wellbeing is important. Read guidance on how to look after your mental wellbeing and mental health.
View Health for further details on healthcare in Turks and Caicos.
